  • here limma (voom method, linear modelling, empirical Bayes moderation) and edgeR package used for differential expression testing.

DF <- read.table("C:/Users/zhang.jing/OneDrive/! Production/TCGA/merge_HTSeq_count/merge_HTSeq_count.txt", sep='\t', header=TRUE, row.names=1, stringsAsFactors = FALSE)

# extract only lung cancer

# add group(tumor or normal tissue) information
dft<-dft %>% separate(sample, c("TCGA", "TSS Code", "participant", "sample","portion", "plate", "center"), "-")
dft$sample <- gsub('[A-Z]','',dft$sample)
dft$sample <- as.numeric(dft$sample)
dft[dft$sample<10,]$sample <- rep('tumor', length(dft[dft$sample<10,]$sample) ) 
dft[which(dft$sample>=10 & dft$sample<=29) ,]$sample <- rep('normal', length(dft[which(dft$sample>=10 & dft$sample<=29) ,]$sample))

dft$sample<-as.factor(dft$sample)
dft<-dft[order(dft$sample,decreasing = FALSE),]

tem <-dft %>% select(-contains(c('TCGA','TSS Code','participant','sample','portion','plate','center')))
df <- as.data.frame(t(tem))

5.2. Making a count matrix, normalization and filtering

filtering and normalization

load("C:/Users/zhang.jing/OneDrive/! Production/TCGA/TCGA_lung.RData")


# create a DGEList object
dge <- DGEList(counts=df, group=group_list)
print(paste('initial data dimention: ', dim(dge)[1], 'x', dim(dge)[2])) # 60482 transcripts, 1145 samples
## [1] "initial data dimention:  60482 x 1145"
lcpm1 <- cpm(dge, log=TRUE) # converting to the log2-scale (normalization step, for plot)

# check transcipts with low counts
print(paste(table(rowSums(dge$counts==0)==1145)[2],'transcipts with low counts, will be filtered'))  # 2158 transcripts have zero counts across all samples
## [1] "2158 transcipts with low counts, will be filtered"
L <- mean(dge$samples$lib.size) * 1e-6 #average library size
M <- median(dge$samples$lib.size) * 1e-6

# remove transcript/gene that consistently have zero or very low counts
keep <- filterByExpr(dge, group_list) # keep CPM >0.2 in at leasAt three samples
dge <- dge[keep,,keep.lib.sizes=FALSE] 
print(paste('filtered data dimention: ', dim(dge)[1], 'x', dim(dge)[2])) # 27753 transcripts, 1145 samples
## [1] "filtered data dimention:  27753 x 1145"
#### normalization
lcpm2 <- cpm(dge, log=TRUE) # converting to the log2-scale

plot and compare filtered data

# density plot before and after filter
lcpm.cutoff <- log2(10/M + 2/L)
nsamples <- ncol(dge)
col <- brewer.pal(nsamples, "Paired")
par(mfrow=c(1,2))

plot(density(lcpm1[,1]), col=col[1], lwd=2, ylim=c(0,0.26), las=2, main="", xlab="")
title(main="A. Raw data", xlab="Log-cpm")
abline(v=lcpm.cutoff, lty=3)

for (i in 2:nsamples){
  den <- density(lcpm1[,i])
  lines(den$x, den$y, col=col[i], lwd=2)}

plot(density(lcpm2[,1]), col=col[1], lwd=2, ylim=c(0,0.26), las=2, main="", xlab="")
title(main="B. Filtered data", xlab="Log-cpm")
abline(v=lcpm.cutoff, lty=3)
  
for (i in 2:nsamples){
  den <- density(lcpm2[,i])
  lines(den$x, den$y, col=col[i], lwd=2)}

5.3. Differential expression analysis

create design matrix and contrasts

group_list <- factor(dft$sample)
design <- model.matrix(~0+group_list)
colnames(design) <- gsub("group_list", "", colnames(design))
rownames(design) <- colnames(df)


contr.matrix <- makeContrasts(
  tumorvsnormal = tumor-normal, 
  levels = colnames(design))
contr.matrix
##         Contrasts
## Levels   tumorvsnormal
##   normal            -1
##   tumor              1

removing heteroscedascity from count data

# voom method (other method : treat )
v <- voom(dge, design, plot=TRUE)

fit  <- lmFit(v, design)
fit  <- contrasts.fit(fit, contrasts=contr.matrix)
efit <- eBayes(fit)

plotSA(efit, main="Final model: Mean-variance trend")

cutoff and save

plotMD(efit, column=1, status=decideTests(efit)[,1], main=colnames(efit)[1], xlim=c(-8,13))

# check : Adjusted p value < 0.05 and |log2fold change (FC)| >2 as cutoff
summary(decideTests(efit,lfc=2,p.value = 0.05)) # 4013 up-regulated gene and 4525 down-regulated gene when using log2fold change (FC)| >1, 1184 up-regulated gene and 1793 down-regulated gene when using log2fold change (FC)| >2. 
##        tumorvsnormal
## Down            1793
## NotSig         24776
## Up              1184
# save
output<-topTable(efit, number =Inf, sort.by = "P") # 27753
output<-output[which(output$adj.P.Val < 0.05 & abs(output$logFC) > 2),] # 2977 DE genes
output<- output[order(output$P.Value, decreasing = FALSE),]

write.table(output, file="Lung_cancer_results/tumor_normal_efit_all.txt", sep='\t', row.names = FALSE, quote = FALSE)

add gene symbol

lookup <- as.character(rownames(efit))
keytypes(org.Hs.eg.db)
##  [1] "ACCNUM"       "ALIAS"        "ENSEMBL"      "ENSEMBLPROT"  "ENSEMBLTRANS"
